34:16.972 --> 34:21.090
Hi. I could sure use one
of those rubdowns tonight.

34:21.226 --> 34:23.329
What's the matter?
Alan get all the townie action, huh?

34:23.353 --> 34:24.559
Oh, geez.

34:28.567 --> 34:30.181
Where's Julie?
Has she come back yet?

34:30.318 --> 34:32.603
I don't know.

34:32.737 --> 34:34.674
So, how in the
hell are we gonna find her?

34:34.697 --> 34:36.418
She's probably gone home.
Come on, let's go.

34:36.449 --> 34:41.784
I'll kick that kid's face,
calling me a fat slob jerk!

34:41.913 --> 34:45.280
And now the part I know
some of you have been waiting for.

34:45.417 --> 34:48.204
This is a traditional part
of our tournament.

34:48.335 --> 34:51.418
So, those of you with your own bikes...

34:51.547 --> 34:54.380
Just what the hell
am I signing away here, man?

34:54.509 --> 34:57.467
Well, your... your intelligence,
your good looks,

34:57.596 --> 34:59.632
and your social standing,
nothing really.

34:59.764 --> 35:02.597
Here, put this on and keep it on.

35:02.726 --> 35:05.342
And if nobody's
up for a direct challenge...

35:05.478 --> 35:07.238
If you don't know
how to write your own name,

35:07.314 --> 35:08.804
why don't you just make an x?

35:11.192 --> 35:12.898
Don't forget to pick up the helmet.

35:13.028 --> 35:16.111
It's the thing that looks like your head,
only it's got a chin strap.

35:18.783 --> 35:20.774
Billy, I...

35:22.078 --> 35:24.740
Aw, man.

35:28.793 --> 35:31.626
You all right? Yeah?

35:33.548 --> 35:36.290
